        <scopecontent>
          <p>Over two hundred, mostly black and white photographs, negatives and slides shot primarily during the 1970s, comprise the Visual Materials series. The images are separated into Grounds, Groups (pictures of campers and staff normally engaged in activities) and Individuals (pictures of one or two campers usually posing for the camera). Also housed here is a 1969 program comprised of slides and a 5 inch reel-to-reel audio tape (3 3/4 ips) documenting activities at Camp Tamarack. The program was created through the School of Education and documents related activities at this camp for university junior high school students located near Ortonville, Michigan.</p>
